aracter-sauron-dweller-nomad-ascetic\">its mysteries</a> \u2014 a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23342914/lord-rings-power-sauron-halbrand\">secret Sauron</a>, a spooky sword, and an <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23327884/rings-power-meteor-stranger-who-is-character-lord-rings-explain", "id": 1261371, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/459369/gandalf-name-saruman-dark-wizard", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Rings of Power season 2 leaves its wizards almost as mysterious as season 1", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T18:29:26+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/until_dawn_remaster.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Developer Ballistic Moon\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24057372/until-dawn-remaster-sony-state-of-play-january-2024\">\u201crebuilt and enhanced\u201d version of horror game <em>Until Dawn</em></a> \u2014&nbsp;out this Friday \u2014&nbsp;goes beyond just a visual upgrade for PlayStation 5 and Windows PC. The remastered re-release of the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2015/8/24/9166487/until-dawn-review-ps4-playstation-4-supermassive-games-horror\">2015 original</a> also includes a little something more, in the form of a new ending that points toward a possible future for the franchise.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">While the studio behind the new <em>Until Dawn</em> has ", "id": 1261372, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/459908/until-dawn-2-remaster-new-ending", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The new Until Dawn is more than just an upgrade, it\u2019s a hint at a sequel", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T18:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A game of Monkey Palace, with many brown Lego arches over a green plate.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo: Ross Miller/Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/IMG_9873.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">When I\u2019m playing board games, I have a habit of photographing the table at the very end, just before we put everything up. There\u2019s something intrinsically rewarding about capturing how a game went from box to setup and then from setup to a full game \u2014 to capture how busy and frenetic everything got, as seen through token-laden boards and stacks of cards in various states of disarray. It\u2019s not that we\u2019ve built anything permanent or long-term impactful, but I love to take time to capture a memory of that experience nonetheless.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a", "id": 1261373, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/459860/monkey-palace-lego-board-game-review", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Asmodee\u2019s first Lego board game, Monkey Palace, feels like Scrabble for STEM kids", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T16:30:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"King Gil-galaad and Elrond covered in blood and looking sad\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Prime Video\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/LOTR_S2_UT_230406_00271_R2_3000.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">So, here we are at last: the eighth and final episode of <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power\"><em>The Rings of Power</em></a><em> </em>season 2. As you\u2019d expect from a season finale, a lot goes down in episode 8. The Sauron/Celebrimbor partnership reaches its inevitably tragic conclusion. The extended dust-up between Elrond, Galadriel, and the elves and Adar\u2019s forces reaches its endgame. And the Stranger finally gets a name.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">With all this payoff, episode 8 should feel like a triumph; the thrilling capsto", "id": 1261375, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/459096/trop-season-finale-review-2-8", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Rings of Power is at battle with itself", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T16:24:59+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/avatarmainimage.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The cycle of death and rebirth continues in the larger world of the Avatar. Paramount Game Studios and Saber Interactive\u00a0announced a new AAA title based on the beloved Nickelodeon animated series <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/avatar-last-airbender\">Avatar: The Last Airbender</a></em> and <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/animation-cartoons/2020/8/31/21405084/legend-of-korra-netflix-bryan-konietzko-michael-dimartino-interview-avatar\">The Legend of Korra</a></em> on Monday. Instead of incorporating established characters like Aang and Korra, the action-RPG title will feature a new story, with players assuming the role of a \u201cnever-before-seen Avatar.\u201d</p>\n\n<", "id": 1261376, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/459981/avatar-last-airbender-new-video-game", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The new Avatar: The Last Airbender\u00a0game sounds super ambitious", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T16:11:07+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/acb97f582afa08d41c44de9d458612dc.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Hot on the heels of Sony\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pre-order/456457/playstation-30th-anniversary-pro-bundle-controller-where-to-buy\">30th anniversary collection</a> of PlayStation hardware and the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pre-order/449691/ps5-pro-ps-direct-amazon-best-buy\">PS5 Pro</a> going up for pre-order, its new, attractive color options for the DualSense and PS5 console covers are about to launch. Dubbed the <a href=\"https://direct.playstation.com/en-us/accessories/ps5/choose-your-color\">Chroma collection</a>, the lineup consists of shiny colorways with hues that shift slightly in the light. White pearl and blue indigo colorway", "id": 1261377, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pre-order/459900/playstation-chroma-dualsense-controller-console-cover-where-to-buy", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The PS5\u2019s colorful, chrome accessories are available to pre-order", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A person holds up five Yu-Gi-Oh cards of different types, fanned out facing the camera.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Photo: Hendrik Schmidt/picture alliance via Getty Images\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/gettyimages-1036448110.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Thousands of cards come through TCGplayer\u2019s Authentication Center in Syracuse, New York, each week. Each and every <em>Magic: The Gathering</em>, Pok\u00e9mon, or Yu-Gi-Oh card on sale at TCGplayer \u2014 the online trading card marketplace that was purchased by eBay in 2022 \u2014 is processed by hand to ensure authenticity and evaluate condition. That work is completed by specialists tasked with inspecting and intaking packages from sellers that amount to anywhere from a handful of cards to 14,000 in a given package. J", "id": 1261378, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/459782/tcgplayer-union-ebay-rally-fair-pay", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The specialists who authenticate trading cards for eBay are rallying for a union contract", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/VXMA_S3_FG_301_00210804_Still445_3000.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">There\u2019s a <em>lot </em>happening in the first three episodes of the new season of <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/sdcc/2024/7/26/24204659/legend-vox-machina-season-3-new-clip\"><em>The Legend of Vox Machina</em></a>: <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23568085/legend-of-vox-machina-chroma-conclave-critical-role-cast-matt-mercer\">duplicitous dragons</a>, reluctant family reunions, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23594728/legend-vox-machina-season-3-villain\">old enemies reappearing</a>, and an unexpected romp to a totally different country, among other things.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">But amid the chase scenes, character introductions (", "id": 1260031, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/458817/legend-vox-machina-cameo-episode-2", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This small scene in Vox Machina episode 2 has added significance to the cast", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/09/GalCel.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Like season 1, <em>The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power</em> season 2 ended with a lot of seismic shifts for the world of Middle-earth. Which makes sense, since <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/454279/trop-magic-gandalf-rings-wasted\">there was a <em>lot</em> covered</a> in the second season of <em>The Rings of Power</em>; between <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/456405/trop-siege-eregion-interview-action-director-vic-armstrong\">a full-on battle</a>, a political coup, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/446640/rings-power-trop-morality-lord-rings\">growing concern about the orc babies at home</a>, and <a href=\"https", "id": 1260032, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/lotr-rings-of-power/459256/trop-season-3-release-date-cast-news", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All the Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power season 3 news we\u2019ve heard so far", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-03T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25482112/1000xresist_principal.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Polygon\u2019s Editor\u2019s Letter is a column from Editor-in-Chief Chris Plante that reflects on the video game and entertainment industries, their communities, and Polygon itself. New editions appear in the first week of each month.</em></p>\n\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Last month, I wrote about how the endless stream of \u201c<a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/opinion/446844/two-ways-to-save-a-video-game-industry-on-fire\">too many games</a>\u201d has caused existential problems for game makers. This month, I\u2019ll focus on the other side of the equation: the audience. The people who play all of these new games. Or, as a <a href", "id": 1260033, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/459580/too-many-video-games", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You will never play many of 2024\u2019s best games", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": nu